{
  "_comment": "Published TASE.2 point model and HMI layout (protocol-agnostic). Each station is one PLC/RTU/feed; each point is one published ICCP indication point. 'type' real -> RealQ float (WRITEF), state -> StateQ integer (WRITEI). 'name' is the ICCP point name the server publishes and the join key to the tag database (ingest/tags*.json), where the SOUTHBOUND PROTOCOL per point is chosen (modbus, dnp3, stub). This one model is therefore universal: the same northbound ICCP points can be fed from Modbus, DNP3, or a mix, just by editing the tag database. 'control' makes a point commandable (kind discrete|setpoint, mode direct|sbo); the server publishes a Block 5 device object <point>_ctl, the HMI operates it, and the gateway writes the command down to the device. Optional 'hi'/'lo' set operator alarm limits in engineering units.",

